abstract: LONGMEADOW, Mass., July 23--The marriage of Miss Carol Sue Riner to Ralph Perlberger took place in Temple B'nai Jacob here this afternoon. Rabbi Haskel Lookstein, assisted by Rabbi Samuel Dresner, performed the ceremony. The bride is a daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Harold L. Riner of Springfield. Mr. Perlberger is a son of Mr. and Mrs. Oscar Perlberger of New York.
headline_main: Carol Sue Riner Wed to Lawyer; 3 Are Attendants

abstract: EASTCHESTER, N.Y., July 21--Peggy Kass of Jumping Brook, won the metropolitan junior girls' golf championship today with a nine-over-par 38, 43-81 over the 5,558-yard Leewood Golf Club course.
headline_main: PEGGY KASS TAKES GIRLS' GOLF TITLE; Cards 81 and Wins by Shot in Metropolitan Tourney

abstract: YONKERS, July 18--In keeping with the apparent theme of this final week of harness racing action of the second of the season's three meetings at Yonkers Raceway, the long shots were decidedly in the limelight tonight. Following the previous night's daily double of $278.40 on a 4-and-2 combination, this evening's payoff on 8 and 2 was a palatable $289.
headline_main: DAILY DOUBLE PAYS $289 AT YONKERS; My Kid, at $66.60, Starts Payoff on 373 $2 Tickets
